<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="421" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,590,1518]" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,950,975]" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">Comments</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1918" box="[342,602,950,974]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Hyperlasion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wasmanni">
<emphasis box="[342,602,950,974]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">Hyperlasion wasmanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by a 1-segmented palpus that is large and swollen, with a large sensory pit of variable shape at the front and a robust curved bristle on the upper border of the pit; rather long antennae; 4 
<superScript attach="left" box="[280,292,1022,1036]" fontSize="6" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">th</superScript>
flagellomere with a l/w index of 2.0, with hairs longer than the basal node; indifferent bristles at the apex of the fore tibia, rather short gonocoxites, with short hairs at the base and the inner ventral margin; gonostylus nearly as long as the gonocoxites, apically rounded, without an apical tooth, with 5–7 short and fine hyaline spines in the distal half.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,590,1518]" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">
<bibRefCitation author="Menzel, F. &amp; Vilkamaa, P. &amp; Smith, J. E." box="[199,435,1169,1194]" pageId="20" pageNumber="421" pagination="283 - 296" refId="ref15994" refString="Menzel, F., Vilkamaa, P. &amp; Smith, J. E. (2013) Overview of the Black Fungus Gnats from the Tristan da Cunha archipelago, including a redescription of Hyperlasion viridiventris (Frey) (Diptera, Sciaroidea: Sciaridae). Contributions to Entomology, 63 (2), 283 - 296." type="journal article" year="2013">
Menzel 
<emphasis box="[292,344,1169,1193]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">et al</emphasis>
. (2013)
</bibRefCitation>
discussed the differences between 
<taxonomicName authority="(Frey, 1945)" authorityName="Frey" authorityYear="1945" baseAuthorityName="Frey" baseAuthorityYear="1945" box="[843,1169,1169,1194]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Hyperlasion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridiventris">
<emphasis box="[843,1017,1169,1193]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">H. viridiventris</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Frey, R." box="[1034,1161,1169,1194]" pageId="20" pageNumber="421" pagination="1 - 114" refId="ref14958" refString="Frey, R. (1945) Tiergeographische Studien uber die Dipterenfauna der Azoren. 1. Verzeichnis der bisher von den Azoren bekannten Dipteren. Societas Scientiarum Fennica Commentationes biologicae, 8 (10), 1 - 114." type="journal article" year="1945">Frey, 1945</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmitz (1918)" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Hyperlasion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wasmanni">
<emphasis box="[1184,1335,1170,1193]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">H. wasmanni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schmitz, H." pageId="20" pageNumber="421" pagination="88 - 111" refId="ref17045" refString="Schmitz, H. (1918) Neue Beitrage zur Kenntnis der Sciariden mit reduzierten Maxillarpalpen. Tijdschrift voor Entomologie, 61 (1 - 2), 88 - 111." type="journal article" year="1918">Schmitz (1918)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Mohrig (2004)" authorityName="Mohrig" authorityYear="2004" box="[284,566,1205,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Hyperlasion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aliens">
<emphasis box="[284,387,1205,1229]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">H. aliens</emphasis>
Mohrig (2004)
</taxonomicName>
. The main characters of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Frey)" authorityName="Frey" baseAuthorityName="Frey" baseAuthorityYear="1945" box="[850,1103,1205,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Hyperlasion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridiventris">
<emphasis box="[850,870,1206,1229]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[886,1023,1205,1229]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">viridiventris</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1032,1041,1205,1230]" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">(</emphasis>
Frey)
</taxonomicName>
are the swollen 1-segmented palpus with a large sensory pit in front and a long and robust curved bristle on the upper margin, rather long flagellomeres and an elongate gonostylus without an apical tooth, but with few (5–7) fine hyaline spines (poorly visible even with a good microscope). The morphological differences with the European specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmitz" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1918" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Hyperlasion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wasmanni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">Hyperlasion wasmanni</emphasis>
Schmitz
</taxonomicName>
are minimal. We think that 
<taxonomicName authority="(Frey)" authorityName="Frey" baseAuthorityName="Frey" baseAuthorityYear="1945" box="[684,900,1349,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Hyperlasion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridiventris">
<emphasis box="[684,821,1349,1373]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">viridiventris</emphasis>
(Frey)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmitz" authorityName="Schmitz" authorityYear="1918" box="[957,1171,1349,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Hyperlasion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="20" pageNumber="421" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wasmanni">
<emphasis box="[957,1070,1350,1373]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="421">wasmanni</emphasis>
Schmitz
</taxonomicName>
are conspecific. In this sense we agree with 
<bibRefCitation author="Hardy, D. E." box="[390,547,1385,1410]" pageId="20" pageNumber="421" pagination="208 - 235" refId="ref15113" refString="Hardy, D. E. (1960) Family Sciaridae. In: Zimmerman, E. C. (Ed.), Insects of Hawaii. A Manual of the Insects of the Hawaiian Islands, including on Enumeration of the Species and Notes on their Origin, Distribution, Hosts, Parasites etc. 10. University Hawaii Press, Honolulu, pp. 208 - 235." type="book chapter" year="1960">Hardy (1960)</bibRefCitation>
: 232 that Tuomikoski also found (in correspondence) that the two species are conspecific. The species is common in open landscapes, and is perhaps connected with ants. The females are often monogenic and in a given period only females are found or a minimal percentage of a population are males.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
